document object module 
The DOM (Document Object Model) is an API that represents and interacts with any HTML or XML-based m.arkup language document. The DOM is a document model loaded in the browser and representing the document as a node tree, or DOM tree, where each node represents part of the document (e.g. an element, text string, or comment)

The addEventListener() method of the EventTarget interface sets up a function that will be called whenever the specified event is delivered to the target

What is Bootstrap? Bootstrap is a free, open source front-end development framework for the creation of websites and web apps. Designed to enable responsive development of mobile-first websites, Bootstrap provides a collection of syntax for template designs.

Bootstrap is the most popular CSS Framework for developing responsive and mobile-first websites.

Bootstrap 5 is the newest version of Bootstrap
What is jumbotron used for?
Jumbotron: How It Works and How Much It Costs to Buy? 
A jumbotron is a large screen or display that is typically used to show video, images, or other types of multimedia content. Jumbotrons are often found in sports stadiums, concert venues, and other large public spaces where people gather to watch live events
